%I A391016 #11 Dec 05 2025 18:23:24
%S A391016 5,1,5,2,0,4,8,3,3,4,1,9
%N A391016 Decimal expansion of an observed ratio describing the separation of level sets in Collatz orbits.
%C A391016 See Sigg link for more information. The constant depends on the validity of the Collatz conjecture and on the persistence of the observed cluster pattern in all level sets of the Collatz tree.
%H A391016 Hugo Pfoertner, <a href="/A391017/a391017_1.txt">Table of n, A391017(n), A391018(n) and product</a>, (2025)
%H A391016 Markus Sigg, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2012.07839">On the cluster structures in Collatz level sets</a>, arXiv:2012.07839 [math.GM], 2020.
%e A391016 0.5152048334...
%o A391016 (PARI) \\ writes improved approximations
%o A391016 my(smin=1); forstep(n=1, oo, 2, my(k=n, s=1); while(k>1, if(k%6==4, s*=(k-1)/k); k=if(k%2, 3*k+1, k>>1)); if(s<smin, printf("%d %18.15f \n", n, s); smin=s))
%Y A391016 Cf. A127824, A391017, A391018.
%K A391016 nonn,cons,more,new
%O A391016 0,1
